Q2. How to set multiple remote repositories for the same project? Explain the use case. you should have a working demo of it.
Answer:
Steps:
1) Clone Your Repository
-> git init

2) Add a Second Remote Repository
-> git remote add Secondary https://gitlab.com/user/repo.git

3) Push to Multiple Repositories
-> git push origin main

Use Cases:
Mirroring repositories
Collaborating with multiple teams
Backup purpose


